parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal has to be reapplied with more pressure
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle does not slow down when applying the brakes
the brakes fail to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel cylinder detached from the mounting point
got caught up in brake shoes
which caused the wheel to freeze up
leading to a rollover accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake shoes can cause the brakes to drag, leading to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brakes drag
there is a strong asbestos odor coming from the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes failed
the vehicle skidded when applying the brakes
the brakes failed during panic stops.

paint flaking off

and back bumper.

intermittent starting issues

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The alternator/generator failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to electrical system failures, stalling, and safety risks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle stalling and brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, and fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause noise, vibration, and decreased performance.
